    "metadata": {
        "6228": {
            "formats": ["EPUB"],
            "format_sizes": {"EPUB": 454967},
            "authors": ["George Lucas", "Chris Claremont"],
            "languages": ["eng"],
            "series": "Chronicles of the Shadow War",
            "publisher": "Bantam Press",
            "rating": 6,
            "tags": ["Fantasy", "Science Fiction"],
            "identifiers": {"google": "xrj3AAAACAAJ", "goodreads": "160859", "isbn": "9780553572858"},
            "author_sort": "Lucas, George & Claremont, Chris",
            "comments": "<div><p>From two of the greatest imaginations of our time comes a magnificent novel of adventure and magic...SHADOW MOON: <em>First in the Chronicles of the Shadow<br>\nWar</em>.  </p>\n<p>The genius of <strong>Star Wars(r)</strong> creator George Lucas and the vision of Chris Claremont, the author of the phenomenally bestselling *The Uncanny<br>\nX-Men<strong>* </strong>adventures, merge in what must be the fantasy event of the year.  </p>\n<p>In <em>Shadow Moon</em>, war and chaos have gripped the land of Tir Asleen. An ancient prophecy reveals one hope: a savior princess who will ascend to the throne when the time is right.  But first, a Nelwyn wanderer must face forces of unimaginable malevolence and dangerous, forbidden rites of necromancy that<br>\ncould bring back a powerful warrior from soulless sleep.  </p>\n<p>George Lucas reshaped filmmaking in the '70s and '80s with his <em>Star Wars</em> and <em>Indiana Jones</em> films.  When Bantam Books asked Lucas if he had any stories he would like to develop as novels rather than as films, Lucas turned to his 1988 fantasy film, <em>Willow</em>.    </p>\n<p>\"When I wrote the story for <em>Willow</em>, I began with the pre-story,\" Lucas said, \"but the full story was yet to be told.\"    </p>\n<p>Now, Lucas's vision is being fulfilled with the talented help of Chris Claremont. Having previously taken the reins of what was for a decade the bestselling comic in the western hemisphere (<em>The Uncanny X-Men</em>) Claremont assumes the reponsibility of foster parent to Lucas's creation.  </p>\n<p>On sale in hardcover now, and available on BDD Audio Cassette as well, SHADOW MOON is a momentous new adventure for readers looking to spend part of this<br>\nsummer in a <em>fantastic</em> world.  SHADOW MOON is one of Bantam Spectra's most exciting publishing events in 1995, the year we celebrate our 10th Anniversary as the premiere publishing imprint of books of speculative fiction.</p></div>",
            "pages": 461,
            "last_modified": "2025-09-24T01:18:59+00:00",
            "pubdate": "1995-01-01T07:00:00+00:00",
            "series_index": 1,
            "sort": "Shadow Moon",
            "size": 454967,
            "timestamp": "2015-10-09T20:37:33+00:00",
            "title": "Shadow Moon",
            "uuid": "95489e58-8c1e-44cc-b3ff-9b9ce3b8d570",
            "urls_from_identifiers": [
                ["Goodreads", "goodreads", "160859", "https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/160859"],
                ["Kobo Metadata", "isbn", "9780553572858", "https://www.kobo.com/us/en/search?query=9780553572858&fcmedia=Book&pageNumber=1&fclanguages=en"],
                ["Google", "google", "xrj3AAAACAAJ", "https://books.google.com/books?id=xrj3AAAACAAJ"],
                ["9780553572858", "isbn", "9780553572858", "https://www.worldcat.org/isbn/9780553572858"]
            ],
